## Simulation Command

--simulate
topology following the CLI
--list-simulation
launch a simulation with the specified
list all the simulations running

## Simulation Parameters

-i, --id <count> specify the id of the simulation (between 0 and 9 included)
-c, --client <count>
specify the number of clients connected to
each satellite terminal
-st, --satellite-terminal <count>
specify the number of terminals in the
emulation
-gw, --gateway <count>
specify the number of the satellite
gateways
-s, --services <count>
specify the services to launch behind the
gateway, the services could be of type "http", service is separated by a coma

## Channel Parameters

-alt, --altitude <delay>
satellite orbit
-p, --params <list_of_parameters>
simulation, they will be specified
specify the delay associated to the
specify the list of parameters of the

## Change a running simulation

--simulation-change <ID> <params>
Modify a running simulation specifying the
ID of the simulation and the parameters

## List of the parameters

-a, --add <ELEMENT>
Add an element to the simulation, the
element could be of type : satellite-terminal, gateway, client or http
-r, --remove <ELEMENT> <ID>
Remove the element specified with its ID
from the simulation
-p, --params
Specify the parameters of the simulation to
change
